Others: Paolo Banchero missed 34 games due to an oblique injury and returned to the Magic lineup on January 11, 2025 against the Milwaukee Bucks.
Banchero scored 34 points and added 7 rebounds in 27 minutes in his first game back.
The Magic lost the game to the Bucks 109-106 despite Banchero's strong performance.
Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 41 points for the Bucks in the game.
Banchero's return to the lineup moved the Magic to the No. 5 spot in the Eastern Conference.
